      "Text": "cockpit security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for cockpit is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Cockpit makes GNU/Linux discoverable. See Linux server in a web browser and perform system tasks with a mouse. Itâ€™s easy to start containers, administer storage, configure networks, and inspect logs with this package.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA flaw was found in the cockpit package. This flaw allows an authenticated user to kill any process when enabling the pam_env's user_readenv option, which leads to a denial of service (DoS) attack.(CVE-2024-6126)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for cockpit is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
